mmad Alternative names Clay, Cassius Marcellus, Jr. Short description American world champion boxer Date of birth January 17, 1942 Place of birth Louisville , Kentucky Date of death Place of death http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Alioldid=596779009 "     Categories : 1942 births Living people African-American boxers African-American Muslims American antiâVietnam War activists American people of Irish descent American conscientious objectors American people of English descent American Sufis Columbia Records artists Counterculture of the 1960s Boxers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Boxers from Kentucky COINTELPRO targets Converts to Islam from Christianity Converts to Sufism Former Nation of Islam members Heavyweight boxers International Boxing Hall of Fame inductees Kentucky colonels Muhammad Ali Olympic boxers of the United States Olympic gold medalists for the United States Olympic medalists in boxing Olympic cauldron lighters People from Cherry Hill, New Jersey People from Paradise Valley, Arizona People with Parkinson's disease Presidential Citizens Medal recipients Presidential Medal of Freedom recipients Professional wrestling referees Sportspeople from Louisville, Kentucky Sportspeople from the Delaware Valley Winners of the United States Championship for amateur boxers World Boxing Association champions World Boxing Council champions World heavyweight boxing champions American male boxers Hidden categories: Pages containing cite templates with deprecated parameters All articles with dead external links Articles with dead external links from September 2011 Articles with inconsistent citation formats Pages containing links to subscription-only content Articles with dead external links from February 2009 Wikipedia indefinitely semi-protected biographies of living people Wikipedia indefinitely move-protected pages Articles with ibid from February 2014 Commons category with local link same as on Wikidata Use mdy dates from October 2012 Wikipedia arti